"{\"uid\": \"voanews.com-a-katie-ledecky-swims-into-olympics-history-winning-800-freestyle-in-paris--7728896.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Share  Share  Print  Every year on August 3, Katie Ledecky is reminded of her first Olympic gold medal.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 103, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 45, \"end\": 58, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Ledecky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She was just 15 years old, a reserved high schooler who had surprisingly made the U.S. swim team for the London Games.\", \"from\": 105, \"to\": 223, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Then she went out and shocked the world, beating everyone in the 800-meter freestyle.\", \"from\": 224, \"to\": 309, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Twelve years to the day, Ledecky did it again.\", \"from\": 311, \"to\": 357, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Not a stunner, but one for the ages.\", \"from\": 359, \"to\": 395, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Gold medal No.\", \"from\": 397, \"to\": 411, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"9.\", \"from\": 412, \"to\": 414, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ledecky capped another stellar Olympics by becoming only the second swimmer to win an event at four straight Summer Games, holding off Ariarne Titmus, the \\\"Terminator,\\\" to win the 800 free Saturday night.\", \"from\": 416, \"to\": 620, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 551, \"end\": 565, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ariarne Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was Ledecky's second gold medal in Paris and the ninth of her remarkable career, which marked another milestone.\", \"from\": 622, \"to\": 737, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 660, \"end\": 665, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3170931730509887e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She became only the sixth Olympian to reach that figure, joining swimmer Mark Spitz, track star Carl Lewis, Soviet gymnast Larisa Latynina, and Finnish runner Paavo Nurmi in a tie for second place.\", \"from\": 739, \"to\": 936, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 765, \"end\": 773, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9969625285354502, \"rank\": 0.0030467258070284234, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 812, \"end\": 822, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Spitz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mark Spitz\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Spitz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Spitz\"}, {\"begin\": 835, \"end\": 845, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carl Lewis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\"}, {\"begin\": 847, \"end\": 853, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soviet_Union\", \"score\": 0.9999999999931788, \"rank\": 5.508526680110592e-12, \"text\": \"Soviet\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soviet_Union\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soviet_Union\"}, {\"begin\": 862, \"end\": 877, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larisa_Latynina\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Larisa Latynina\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larisa_Latynina\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larisa_Latynina\"}, {\"begin\": 883, \"end\": 890, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Finland\", \"score\": 0.9999992590886011, \"rank\": 4.4929119756271556e-07, \"text\": \"Finnish\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Finland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Finland\"}, {\"begin\": 898, \"end\": 909, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paavo_Nurmi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paavo Nurmi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paavo_Nurmi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paavo_Nurmi\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The only athlete to win more golds: swimmer Michael Phelps with 23.\", \"from\": 938, \"to\": 1005, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 982, \"end\": 996, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.053377064362952e-105, \"text\": \"Michael Phelps\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ledecky was very aware of the significance of the date.\", \"from\": 1007, \"to\": 1062, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Every August 3rd, the video [of her first Olympic gold] gets posted somewhere and you kind of reminisce,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 1064, \"to\": 1180, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"So, when I saw it was August 3rd, I was like, 'Oh boy, I have got to get the job done.'\\\"\", \"from\": 1181, \"to\": 1270, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That she did, going faster than her winning time in Tokyo to finish in 8 minutes, 11.04 seconds.\", \"from\": 1272, \"to\": 1368, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1324, \"end\": 1329, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999999999290594, \"rank\": 7.088676810838176e-11, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Titmus was right on her shoulder nearly the entire race, but Ledecky pulled away in the final 100.\", \"from\": 1369, \"to\": 1467, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1369, \"end\": 1375, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Titmus, who beat Ledecky in the 400 freestyle, settled for silver at 8:12.29.\", \"from\": 1469, \"to\": 1546, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1469, \"end\": 1475, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The bronze went to another American, Paige Madden at 8:13.00.\", \"from\": 1547, \"to\": 1608, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1574, \"end\": 1582, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9997729723168655, \"rank\": 0.00022471055462751276, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1584, \"end\": 1596, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paige_Madden\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paige Madden\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paige_Madden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paige_Madden\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Phelps had been the only swimmer to win the same event at four straight Olympics, taking gold in the 200 individual medley at Athens, Beijing, London and Rio de Janeiro.\", \"from\": 1610, \"to\": 1779, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1610, \"end\": 1616, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\", \"score\": 0.9999994888909383, \"rank\": 5.111091654929891e-07, \"text\": \"Phelps\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\"}, {\"begin\": 1736, \"end\": 1742, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7681283403348885e-21, \"text\": \"Athens\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1744, \"end\": 1751, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.969240556000055e-24, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1753, \"end\": 1759, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999309393411, \"rank\": 3.832088965893866e-08, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 1764, \"end\": 1778, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.771360834031669e-23, \"text\": \"Rio de Janeiro\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Now he's got company.\", \"from\": 1781, \"to\": 1802, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Titmus added some perspective to Ledecky's consistency over the last dozen years, noting where she was when the American won that first gold in London.\", \"from\": 1804, \"to\": 1955, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1804, \"end\": 1810, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\"}, {\"begin\": 1916, \"end\": 1924, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9997729723168655, \"rank\": 0.00022471055462751276, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1948, \"end\": 1954, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999309393411, \"rank\": 3.832088965893866e-08, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was in grade six in primary school,\\\" Titmus said.\", \"from\": 1957, \"to\": 2009, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1997, \"end\": 2003, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That's how remarkable she is.\\\"\", \"from\": 2010, \"to\": 2041, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Their friendly rivalry has driven both to greater heights.\", \"from\": 2043, \"to\": 2101, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They each won two golds and four medals at these games, which pushed Ledecky to 14 overall and left the 23-year-old Aussie with four golds and eight medals in her career.\", \"from\": 2102, \"to\": 2272, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"To think that eight years later, I challenged her into her fourth consecutive in the 800 is pretty cool,\\\" Titmus said.\", \"from\": 2274, \"to\": 2393, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2381, \"end\": 2387, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"So I am really proud of myself and I feel very honored and privileged to be her rival, and I hope I have made her a better athlete.\", \"from\": 2394, \"to\": 2526, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She has certainly made me become the athlete I am.\", \"from\": 2527, \"to\": 2577, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I felt so privileged to race alongside her.\\\"\", \"from\": 2578, \"to\": 2622, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dominant for a dozen years  Ledecky has dominated the distance freestyle events over the last dozen years - and is not done yet.\", \"from\": 2624, \"to\": 2752, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She's made it clear she plans to keep swimming at least through the 2028 Los Angeles Games.\", \"from\": 2753, \"to\": 2844, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's not easy,\\\" Ledecky said.\", \"from\": 2848, \"to\": 2878, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I will take it year by year, and we will see if I can keep giving everything I have got for as long as I have left in me.\\\"\", \"from\": 2879, \"to\": 3002, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Another gold for Canadian teenager  Summer McIntosh stamped herself as one of the swimming stars of the Paris Olympics with her third individual gold medal, winning the 200 individual medley.\", \"from\": 3004, \"to\": 3195, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3021, \"end\": 3029, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"score\": 0.9999991954012839, \"rank\": 8.045991748259381e-07, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\"}, {\"begin\": 3040, \"end\": 3055, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Summer McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 17-year-old Canadian chased down American Alex Walsh and held off another U.S. swimmer, Kate Douglass, to finish in an Olympic record of 2:06.56.\", \"from\": 3197, \"to\": 3346, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3213, \"end\": 3221, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"score\": 0.9999991954012839, \"rank\": 8.045991748259381e-07, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\"}, {\"begin\": 3234, \"end\": 3242, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9997729723168655, \"rank\": 0.00022471055462751276, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 3243, \"end\": 3253, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexandra_Walsh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alex Walsh\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexandra_Walsh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexandra_Walsh\"}, {\"begin\": 3289, \"end\": 3302, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kate Douglass\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Douglass grabbed the silver in the star-studded final at 2:06.92, but the Americans lost the bronze when Walsh, the silver medalist in this event at Tokyo who recorded a time of 2:07.06, was disqualified because she did not finish the backstroke segment on her back.\", \"from\": 3348, \"to\": 3614, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3348, \"end\": 3356, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stu_Douglass\", \"score\": 0.9854807171330573, \"rank\": 0.014733198341389557, \"text\": \"Douglass\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stu_Douglass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stu_Douglass\"}, {\"begin\": 3497, \"end\": 3502, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999999999290594, \"rank\": 7.088676810838176e-11, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kaylee McKeown, who touched fourth, was bumped up to the bronze at 2:08.08.\", \"from\": 3616, \"to\": 3691, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3616, \"end\": 3630, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylee_McKeown\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kaylee McKeown\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylee_McKeown\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylee_McKeown\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was a bitter blow for Walsh, whose younger sister, Gretchen, has won a gold medal and two silvers in Paris.\", \"from\": 3693, \"to\": 3803, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3747, \"end\": 3755, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gretchen_Walsh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.0018849187558986e-22, \"text\": \"Gretchen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gretchen_Walsh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gretchen_Walsh\"}, {\"begin\": 3797, \"end\": 3802, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3170931730509887e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"McIntosh set several world records ahead of the Paris Olympics, and she backed up the enormous expectations by claiming a starring role at La Defense Arena along with L\\u00e9on Marchand and Ledecky.\", \"from\": 3805, \"to\": 3998, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3805, \"end\": 3813, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"score\": 0.9999999902702257, \"rank\": 9.729963873698729e-09, \"text\": \"McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\"}, {\"begin\": 3972, \"end\": 3985, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/L\\u00e9on_Marchand\", \"score\": 0.9999997803538704, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"L\\u00e9on Marchand\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/L\\u00e9on_Marchand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/L\\u00e9on_Marchand\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"McIntosh also won gold medals in the 200 butterfly and 400 IM, plus a silver in the 400 freestyle.\", \"from\": 4000, \"to\": 4098, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4000, \"end\": 4008, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"score\": 0.9999999902702257, \"rank\": 9.729963873698729e-09, \"text\": \"McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She fell just 0.88 seconds - the margin of her loss to Titmus - shy of matching Marchand's four individual golds.\", \"from\": 4099, \"to\": 4212, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4179, \"end\": 4187, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"score\": 0.9999999878459677, \"rank\": 1.201483571426363e-08, \"text\": \"Marchand\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q11774891\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's pretty surreal,\\\" said McIntosh, who became the first Canadian athlete to win three golds in a single Olympics.\", \"from\": 4214, \"to\": 4330, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4242, \"end\": 4250, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"score\": 0.9999999902702257, \"rank\": 9.729963873698729e-09, \"text\": \"McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\"}, {\"begin\": 4273, \"end\": 4281, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"score\": 0.9999991954012839, \"rank\": 8.045991748259381e-07, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am just so proud of myself and how I have been able to recover and manage events.\", \"from\": 4331, \"to\": 4415, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"US sets world recordThe United States made up for a disappointing showing in Tokyo by setting a world record in the 4x100 mixed medley relay.\", \"from\": 4417, \"to\": 4558, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4417, \"end\": 4419, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"s